<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="310" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1590,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1590,1616]" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. In the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck, W." box="[436,631,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="310" refId="ref14900" refString="Lundbeck, W. (1922) Diptera Danica Part VI Pipunculidae, Phoridae. Wesley, London, 447 pp." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
to Group IV it runs to couplet 30 lead 2 or couplet 45 lead 2, but both options differ in their hypopygia. In the key to the males of species from the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney R. H. L." box="[1169,1320,1627,1653]" pageId="4" pageNumber="310" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref14009" refString="Disney R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 10 (8), Royal Entomologicai Society of London, 1 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631287 X 00115" type="book chapter" year="1989">Disney, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 143 lead 1, but is immediately distinguished by its yellow legs and other details. In the keys of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz H. &amp; Beyer" pageId="4" pageNumber="310" pagination="513 - 608" refId="ref15062" refString="Schmitz H. &amp; Beyer (1965) Phoridae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33) (Lieferung 258, 260). E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 513 - 608." type="book chapter" year="1965">Schmitz &amp; Beyer (1965)</bibRefCitation>
for Abteilung IV, Zweite Reihe it will run to couplets 66, 85 or 97, but differs from the species of these couplets in terms of the combination of their yellow legs, differing hypopygia and other details. It fails to run down in keys for the rest of the world’s fauna and subsequent additions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="4" pageNumber="310" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1590,1977]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="313" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1806,1832]" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[518,660,1806,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">Figs 35 &amp; 36</figureCitation>
and with the very fine microtrichia restricted to the edges and adjacent to the median furrow. Cheek with 3 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, with a few large SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[622,703,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
. Thorax as 
<figureCitation box="[829,910,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
, with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these; mesopleuron with hairs; and scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites brown with fine hairs, but longer more robust hairs at rear of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1181,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="310">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Venter gray, and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[613,743,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="313">Figs 39–42</figureCitation>
, the right hypandrial lobe being vestigial. Legs yellow. Fore tarsus (
<figureCitation box="[231,311,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="313">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–5. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.8 times its length (
<figureCitation box="[335,419,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="313">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[602,683,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="313">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with about 10 differentiated posterodorsal hairs, the first 3–4 being fine, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1177,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[186,1402,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Megaselia dravedskovensis n. sp. male. 35, frons; 36, detail of frons with lack of microtrichia; 37, postpedicels, palp and proboscis; 38, left face of thorax; 39–42, hypopygium; 43, front tarsus; 44, mid tibia and basitarsus; 45, hind femur; 46, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925227" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925227/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="313">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[1193,1293,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="7" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="1.85">1.85 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.46. Costal ratios 3.4:2.5:1 Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[841,942,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="0.18">0.18 mm</quantity>
long. Hair at base of vein 3 
<quantity box="[1270,1372,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long. With 3 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[651,751,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="313" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob pale brownish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
